    • Field Detail

      • Default

        public static final PDFOptions Default
        Constant with the most common PDF export configuration options already set. The values for the various configuration options are defined as follows:
        • Row Labels: true
        • Column Labels: true
        • Ignore Empty Rows: false
        • Ignore Empty Columns: false
        • Date-Time Format Pattern: MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm a
        • Paged: true
        • Page Numbers: true
        • Page Width: 8.5"
        • Page Height: 11"
        • Default Column Width: 65px
        • Sticky Row Labels: true
        • Sticky Column Labels: true
        • Default Font Size: 8px
        • Default Font Family: Helvetica

        To include these default values when exporting to PDF, simply include PDFOptions.Default in the import factory method or supporting TableElement export method.

        See Also:
        Table#export(String, BaseIOOptions), Table#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOptions), Row#export(String, BaseIOOptions), Row#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOptions), Column#export(String, BaseIOOptions), Column#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOptions), Subset#export(String, BaseIOOptions), Subset#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOptions)
